e .resources files for strings and objects.","pos":[7378,7452]},{"pos":[7457,7472],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>-culture:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>de","source":"**-culture:**de"},{"content":"Specifies the culture of the resource to compile.","pos":[7473,7522]},{"content":"The common language runtime uses this information when it searches for the resources for a specified culture.","pos":[7523,7632]},{"content":"If you omit this option, Al.exe will still compile the resource, but the runtime will not be able to find it when a user requests it.","pos":[7633,7766]},{"pos":[7771,7801],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>-out:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>Example.resources.dll","source":"**-out:**Example.resources.dll"},{"content":"Specifies the name of the output file.","pos":[7802,7840]},{"content":"The name must follow the naming standard <bpt id=\"p1\">*</bpt>baseName<ept id=\"p1\">*</ept>.resources.<bpt id=\"p2\">*</bpt>extension<ept id=\"p2\">*</ept>, where <bpt id=\"p3\">*</bpt>baseName<ept id=\"p3\">*</ept> is the name of the main assembly and <bpt id=\"p4\">*</bpt>extension<ept id=\"p4\">*</ept> is a valid file name extension (such as .dll).","pos":[7841,8028],"source":" The name must follow the naming standard *baseName*.resources.*extension*, where *baseName* is the name of the main assembly and *extension* is a valid file name extension (such as .dll)."},{"content":"Note that the runtime is not able to determine the culture of a satellite assembly based on its output file name; you must use the <bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>/culture<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept> option to specify it.","pos":[8029,8194],"source":" Note that the runtime is not able to determine the culture of a satellite assembly based on its output file name; you must use the **/culture** option to specify it."},{"pos":[8199,8224],"content":"<bpt id=\"p1\">**</bpt>-template:<ept id=\"p1\">**</ept>Example.dll","source":"**-template:**Example.dll"},{"content":"Specifies an assembly from which the satellite assembly 