lture* is the name of the culture whose resources the satellite assembly contains."},{"content":"Visual Studio handles this process automatically.","pos":[13139,13188]},{"content":"You can then run the example.","pos":[13195,13224]},{"content":"It will randomly make one of the supported cultures the current culture and display a localized greeting.","pos":[13225,13330]},{"pos":[13360,13420],"content":"Installing Satellite Assemblies in the Global Assembly Cache","linkify":"Installing Satellite Assemblies in the Global Assembly Cache","nodes":[{"content":"Installing Satellite Assemblies in the Global Assembly Cache","pos":[0,60]}]},{"content":"Instead of installing assemblies in a local application subdirectory, you can install them in the global assembly cache.","pos":[13424,13544]},{"content":"This is particularly useful if you have class libraries and class library resource assemblies that are used by multiple applications.","pos":[13545,13678]},{"content":"Installing assemblies in the global assembly cache requires that they have strong names.","pos":[13685,13773]},{"content":"Strong-named assemblies are signed with a valid public/private key pair.","pos":[13774,13846]},{"content":"They contain version information that the runtime uses to determine which assembly to use to satisfy a binding request.","pos":[13847,13966]},{"content":"For more information about strong names and versioning, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Assembly Versioning<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/app-domains/assembly-versioning.md)</ept>.","pos":[13967,14109],"source":" For more information about strong names and versioning, see [Assembly Versioning](../../../docs/framework/app-domains/assembly-versioning.md)."},{"content":"For more information about strong names, see <bpt id=\"p1\">[</bpt>Strong-Named Assemblies<ept id=\"p1\">](../../../docs/framework/app-domains/strong-named-assemblies.md)</ept>.","pos":[14110,14245],"source":" For more information about strong names, see [Strong-Named